<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="8eca3525-34f2-5670-b6f2-177cde3e34e3" activityNameId="56c91ddd-29a0-42b2-9096-eaba838e338e" parentActivityId="1cc14b06-6481-5096-8567-3a8184034260" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">N-methyl-2-pyrrolidone production</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts when the raw materials enter the process.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">Materials entering the process are included as well as energy uses, infrastructure and emissions.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Methylpyrolidone is mainly used as a solvent. Other areas of use are in the processing of petroleum distillates, engineering plastics, paints, chemicals for agriculture application, electronics, and as a component of cleaning agents (Harreus et al. 2011).</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="28f738cc-bb73-48f8-b633-f83fb9bc5ddc">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2011:Manufacture of basic chemicals</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="0723d252-7e2a-11de-9820-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">RER</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The inputs to the process are calculated based on stoichiometry and literature data, they are therefore considered to be valid for the chosen geography. The inputs of heat, electricity, water, factory and nitrogen are mostly taken as average of industry data. Industry data values are a 5-year average of data (2011 - 2015) published by the Gendorf factory (Gendorf, 2016, Umwelterklärung, www.gendorf.de), (Gendorf, 2015, Umwelterklärung, www.gendorf.de), (Gendorf, 2014, Umwelterklärung, www.gendorf.de). The Gendorf factory is based in Germany, it produces a wide range of chemical substances. The factory produced 1657400 tonnes of chemical substances in the year 2015 (Gendorf, 2016, Umwelterklärung, www.gendorf.de) and 740000 tonnes of intermediate products. As, according to Cefic Report of the chemical industry (Cefic 2016. Facts and figures 2016 of the European chemical industry. Accessible at: http://www.cefic.org/Facts-and-Figures/Chemicals-Industry-Profile/, accessed 30/06/2017), Germany covers 28.5% of EU chemical generated sales in 2015, we assumed these values to be representative of the RER geography. </text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The main production route for methylpyrolidone is the reaction of gamma-Butyrolactone and methylamine. The reaction takes place in a high-pressure tube, with pressure between 6 and 12 MPa. The exothermic reaction requires temperatures between 250 and 400 degrees Celsius. This reaction is often an adiabatic process. The product of this reaction is then decompressed and distilled. The efficiency of the reaction is over 97% (Harreus et al. 2011).</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2015-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true"/>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
