        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Estimated value. The Global production volume is estimated based on information from Cefic (European Chemical Industry Council) and the American Chemistry Council. 
According to Cefic (2016) the Global sales of chemicals in the year 2015 was 3,534 billion euros. The reported share of sales per regions are: EU28 14.7%; Other Europe (Switzerland, Norway, Turkey, Russia and Ukraine) 2.7%; NAFTA (USA, Canada and Mexico) 16.5%; Latin America 3.8%; China 39.9%; Japan 3.9%; Republic of Korea 3.2%; India 2.2%; Rest of Asia 11.9%; Rest of the World 1.3%. Cefic also reports the USA total sales, 518.7 billion euros of the global 3534 billion euros (14.7%). The same share is reported from the American Chemistry Council (2016), according to this source the USA sales account for 15% of global sales for the year 2016. 

Literature value. Harreus et al. 2011 report a word capacity of 200 to 250 thousand tons per year, the main producers reported are: BASF, ISP, Lyondell-Basell, and Mitsubishi. The Chinese production is predicted to increase (Harreus et al. 2011).

The European production volume is calculated based on the RER share of global sales, which is here defined as EU28 plus Other Europe, share of sales (14.7% + 2.7% = 17.4%).

Reference(s):
Cefic 2016. Facts and figures 2016 of the European chemical industry. Accessible at: http://www.cefic.org/Facts-and-Figures/Chemicals-Industry-Profile/, accessed 1 March 2017
American Chemistry Council 2016. Outlook: U.S. Chemical Industry Continues to Outpace Industrial Output; Accounts for More Than One-Half of Construction Spending by Manufacturing Sector. Accessible at: https://www.americanchemistry.com/Media/PressReleasesTranscripts/ACC-news-releases/US-Chemical-Industry-Continues-to-Outpace-Industrial-Output.html, accessed 1 March 2017
Harreus, A.L. et al. 2011. 2-Pyrrolidone. In Ullmann's Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry, Electronic Release, pp.2-4. Wiley-VCH, Weinheim</productionVolumeComment>
